This paper is about developing a real-time, high-quality video object segmentation algorithm using a novel global context module. The paper focuses on computer vision and machine learning techniques to achieve this goal, which suggests that it is most likely to belong to the cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) sub-category. Additionally, the paper discusses the use of deep learning models and optimization techniques, which are common in the cs.LG (Machine Learning) sub-category. The paper also mentions the use of semi-supervised learning, which is a common topic in the cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) sub-category. The paper's focus on video object segmentation suggests that it could also belong to the cs.MM (Multimedia) sub-category. Finally, the paper's discussion of real-time processing suggests that it could also belong to the cs.RO (Robotics) sub-category, which often deals with real-time processing and control.
